I think that Arch Linux is the best distro I tried - it's fast, stable, and very simple to use and maintain even for newbies (ArchWiki is excellent though some parts are chaotic)<br />Pacman have very simple syntax and it's easy to use - on top of that, great community and AUR<br />Only downside that I experienced is that sometimes update can mess with your system and packages, but it's always quickly solved by Arch community (main site, forums)<br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
