<td width=30% style="border:0" valign=top>
<b>Version:</b> current<br /><b>Rating:</b> 10<br /><b>Date:</b> 2020-04-07<br /><b>Votes:</b> 9<br /><br /><br /></td>
<td width="70%" style="border:0" valign="top">
I switched from Debian to Arch linux two years ago, because I wanted to have a system that is always up-to-date and one, where I don''t need to upgrade from version to version. Arch runs very stable and with the AUR, a community driven repository, you get almost every software you need.<br /><br />The documentary is awesome and helps you much better than reading through forums. I encourage everyone who already used other distros and has some linux knowledge to install this operating system. Once installed it's runs really smooth. For installing the distro there is a good tutorial provided by the arch wiki.<br /><br />Something negative? No, nothing.<br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
