<td width="70%" style="border:0" valign="top">
Great distro for people that like to tweak things and make it their own. Arch is not a dristro for new users that want everything to work out of the box, but it is really good if you are willing to read the Arch wiki when installing it (and everything else you need) and if you are willing to look at the front page before updating. If you just do what it tells you to do of manual intervnetion on their front page before upgrading, it is rock solid.<br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
