<tr style="outline: thin solid black">
<td width=30% style="border:0" valign=top>
<b>Version:</b> current<br /><b>Rating:</b> 10<br /><b>Date:</b> 2020-03-16<br /><b>Votes:</b> 2<br /><br /><br /></td>
<td width="70%" style="border:0" valign="top">
For me this is the best distro ever and I feel to recommend it to anyone who has just a little bit of patience and time to read the wiki carefully before installing.<br />It has the fame of being 'user unfriendly' and 'unstable', but it's not the case.<br />The installation is the only thing that may require a little bit of basic knowledge on how to partition a drive, etc, and it may take a little bit more of time and effort to be installed as opposed to more 'mainsteam' distros, but on the other hand the CLI installation is not that hard and will provide a great way to build your system from the ground up, giving the user total freedom.<br />After the installation its surprisingly easy to use and mantain. The idea behind it is that everithing should be as simple and barebone as possible, so the user can understand the system and operate with more freedom. Sometimes it may look more complicated, but actually it's not. The reason why it may give that impession is that it doesn't hide the layers of complexity to the user, so at the end it's really simpler that other distros, even those known to be more 'user friendly'.<br />Package management is one of the best things under Arch, the pacman package manager is awesome: fast, easy to use and very powerfull. <br />Repos are updated frequently, so that you don't end up with old and custy packages that can cause dependency poblems.<br />It's a rolling release distro, but also very stable: the only thing to keep in mind is to take a look at the Arch homepage before upgrading the system to see if some package require manual intervention (it seems to be a rare occurence anyway).<br />The Arch wiki is probably the best and more usefull, even if you don't run arch.<br />If you ar looking for a rolling release distro then look no further: Arch is the best.<br /><br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
