<td width=30% style="border:0" valign=top>
<b>Version:</b> current<br /><b>Rating:</b> 10<br /><b>Date:</b> 2020-03-06<br /><b>Votes:</b> 0<br /><br /><br /></td>
<td width="70%" style="border:0" valign="top">
Arch Linux is, literally, what you make of it. Considering that it's a rolling distro, it's very stable. You have to know what you're doing, though, which is great, in my opinion. Arch also seems to be the testing zone for new releases of Linux software across the Internet.<br /><br />Some of the comments complain about AUR packages, but Arch Linux doesn't support AUR packages. There's no reason to complain about them since it's obvious from the site and documentation that you're completely on your own there. I wouldn't want to live without it, though.<br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
