<td width=30% style="border:0" valign=top>
<b>Version:</b> current<br /><b>Rating:</b> 9<br /><b>Date:</b> 2019-12-28<br /><b>Votes:</b> 6<br /><br /><br /></td>
<td width="70%" style="border:0" valign="top">
Arch is a perfect meta-distribution. It provides an excellent base for more customized distributions such as Manjaro and many others.<br />With that said, I would not recommend it to anyone who wants to simply 'use' Linux. It requires too much work to fully install and configure for one's specific hardware and needs and even Linux old timers may feel that they are simply 'too lazy' to install it and set it up.<br /><br />Arch is for those who want to learn to configure every part of their system and have 'absolute' control over their systems, but unless this is you, it simply requires too much work to set up and personalize, especially on modern laptops.<br /><br />Pacman is superb and the Arch documentation is second to none, I wish there would be many more distributions based on Arch, but customized for less generic purposes while still compatible with the excellent AUR.<br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
