As a Linux newbie I have been able to setup Arch and the KDE desktop as my daily driver following tutorials and reading many forums. <br />It runs amazingly well and I'm loving using it. <br />It does breaks sometimes, usually self inflicted stupidity, but understanding the setup process makes it easier to understand the fixes as well.<br /><br />Some slight challenges were...<br />    - Getting Creative EMU PCI 1820m soundcard working.<br />      (Still yet to try and get input from Dock to a DAW and scared to try Jack setup!!)<br />    - Getting dual boot on a soft SSD Raid setup to work.<br />    - Weird stop message when I turn on the computer. Have to reset and then it boots up fine!?!<br />      (Still don't know why!)<br /><br />My first impression of the community is that they can be helpful, but they do assume a lot, even on the newbie pages. I don't think that's an Arch linux exclusive problem though!<br /><br />Most AUR packages work great but have had 2 fail so far and no response yet from the authors.<br /><br />There were challenges but there is very little reason for me to boot up my Windows partition now. Only use it to chkdsk my ntfs partition now when it decides to become non-writable in Linux!<br /><br />I don't want to distro hop and love the Arch concept of adding what you want only and the rolling updates. Using Timeline as my backup tool in case I bork something gives me some peace of mind as well.<br />Hoping that I can ditch Windows for good with Arch! :)<br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
