<td width="70%" style="border:0" valign="top">
Fantastic Distribution. Stable, fast and precise, and the way it's built means you can dictate exactly what you want installed on the PC outside of the base installation packages.<br /><br />AUR is the superior way of handling packages that aren't in the main repo, rather than Ubuntu's messy PPAs for example.<br /><br />Pacman is a great CLI package manager, and if everything is kept up to date then no problems should arise.<br /><br />Needs a lot of patience and some technical know-how to get it installed, but well worth the effort in learning, and stands out alongside vanilla Debian as one of the two ways Linux should be used: Cutting edge vs stability.<br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
