Arch is my favorite distro for regular use! Once you learn how to set it up and get really familiar with Arch the experience is awesome. The best part is you can make it your own! You have near full control over every aspect of your system, but it isn't very difficult to get a working system with the setup guide. I have used Arch almost exclusively for a couple of years now on several machines and have had great stability even though it is rolling release. The best thing is that I always have the latest software and kernel instead of being back in the stone age as with a lot of other distros. <br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
