<td width="70%" style="border:0" valign="top">
I used Ubuntu and afterwards Mint before I switched to Arch for good a couple of years ago. The customization possibilities are endless and you can tailor your system to be just what you need, not more and not less, and while you do so you learn a lot about Linux. Setting it up for the first time takes a while but afterwards I set up all my machines to run on Arch. The wiki is the best wiki I've seen so far and pacman is plain awesome.<br /><br /><br /><form name=like method=get>
